ZCZC GE10
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 212300 UTC
THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY A LARGE AREA OF HIGH
PRESSURE WILL REMAIN OVER SERN EUROPE. AN AREA OF LOW
PRESSURE WILL MOV TOWARDS ICELAND AND DEEPEN TO 954.
ASSOCIATED FRONTAL TROUGHS WILL SPREAD ACROSS THE UK.
THROUGH MONDAY A FRONTAL LOW PRESSURE CENTRE WILL SPREAD
ACROSS IRELAND AND SCOTLAND FOLLOWED BY A TRANSITORY
RIDGE ON TUESDAY AS THE LOW PRESSURE CENTRE MIGRATES TO
THE NORWEGIAN SEA. PRESSURE WILL REMAIN HIGH OVER SERN
EUROPE WITH PRESSURE REMAINING LOW TO THE W OF ICELAND.
THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY SW WINDS WILL BE OCNL
STRG IN ALL SEA AREAS PERHAPS WITH GALES BY SUNDAY
EVENING IN VIKING AND FAIR ISLE. ON MONDAY WINDS WILL
INCREASE WITH GALES DEVELOPING LATER IN ALL SEA AREAS
PERHAPS SEV GALES OR STORMS IN THE N AND W OF THE N SEA.
WINDS WILL TEND TO DECREASE ON TUESDAY BUT STILL STRG AT
TIMES LATER
